<doc id="433984" wikidata="Q2468645" url="?curid=433984" title="USS Birmingham">
<text>Three ships of the United States Navy have been named Birmingham, after the city of Birmingham, Alabama.

* , was a light cruiser in service from 1908 to 1923.
* , was a light cruiser commissioned in 1943, involved in heavy fighting in the Pacific War, and decommissioned in 1946.
* , was a &quot;Los Angeles&quot;-class nuclear attack submarine in service from 1978 to 1997.

